de.uka.ipd.sdq.beagle.measurement.kieker.instrumentation

Interface EclipseAstInstrumentationStrategy

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ResourceDemandInstrumentationStrategy

    public interface EclipseAstInstrumentationStrategy
    Defines how to instrument a code section by providing AST statements to insert before and after the section.

    • Method Summary

    • Method Detail

      • instrumentStart

        org.eclipse.jdt.core.dom.Statement instrumentStart(CodeSection codeSection,
                                                   org.eclipse.jdt.core.dom.AST nodeFactory)
        Provides a node to be inserted before the given codeSection. The statement returned is to be inserted before the first statement of the given codeSection.
        Parameters:
        codeSection - The section being instrumented.
        nodeFactory - The AST instance that must be used to create the instrumentation statement.
        Returns:
        The statement to add directly before the code section. The returned statement’s ASTNode.getAST() must return nodeFactory. null to not insert anything.

      • instrumentEnd

        org.eclipse.jdt.core.dom.Statement instrumentEnd(CodeSection codeSection,
                                                 org.eclipse.jdt.core.dom.AST nodeFactory)
        Provides a node to be inserted after the given codeSection. The statement returned is to be inserted after the last statement of the given codeSection.
        Parameters:
        codeSection - The section being instrumented.
        nodeFactory - The AST instance that must be used to create the instrumentation statement.
        Returns:
        The statement to add directly after the code section. The returned statement’s ASTNode.getAST() must return nodeFactory. null to not insert anything.
